# **Feasibility Framework for the FORGE‑LIVE Multiverse**

## **1. Start With the Core: Live, Protected Creation**
The first milestone is simple and powerful:  
A **single creation station** where you build live, with automatic copyright protection and continuity anchoring.

This gives you:

- **[proof of concept](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20proof%20of%20concept)**  
- **[public visibility](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20public%20visibility)**  
- **[artifact generation](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20artifact%20generation)**  
- **[investor traction](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20investor%20traction)**  

This is the ignition point.

---

## **2. Add the Station Architecture**
Once the first creation station is running, you introduce the station model:

- **[project stations](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20project%20stations)**  
- **[event stations](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20event%20stations)**  
- **[showcase stations](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20showcase%20stations)**  
- **[idea carousel stations](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20idea%20carousel%20stations)**  
- **[protocol carousel stations](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20protocol%20carousel%20stations)**  

This creates the **ecosystem structure** without needing the full ecosystem on day one.

---

## **3. Introduce the Protected Creator Economy**
Next, you enable basic creator interactions:

- **[show your work](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20show%20your%20work)**  
- **[pitch ideas](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20pitch%20ideas)**  
- **[collaborate safely](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20collaborate%20safely)**  
- **[hire or volunteer](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20hire%20or%20volunteer)**  

This turns the platform from a show into a **marketplace**.

---

## **4. Add Transaction Mechanics**
Once creators are active, you introduce monetization:

- **[purchase ideas on the fly](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20purchase%20ideas%20on%20the%20fly)**  
- **[pre‑order ideas](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20pre%E2%80%91order%20ideas)**  
- **[book creator time blocks](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20book%20creator%20time%20blocks)**  
- **[license artifacts](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20license%20artifacts)**  

This creates the **innovation commerce layer**.

---

## **5. Launch Live Solve Competitions**
These accelerate adoption and innovation:

- **[protected competitions](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20protected%20competitions)**  
- **[volunteer sessions](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20volunteer%20sessions)**  
- **[speed‑round training](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20speed%E2%80%91round%20training)**  
- **[rapid problem solving](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20rapid%20problem%20solving)**  

This is where the ecosystem becomes **alive**.

---

## **6. Introduce Live Crypto Build Sessions**
Once the innovation engine is running, you add:

- **[live token evolution](guide://action?prefill=Tell%20me%20more%20about%3A%20live%20token%20evolution)**  
